eventgrp.event:
Wrote for Life Illustrated;
              published second edition of Leaves of
                Grass

scopecontent.p:
Description from Frey: Eleven autograph letters, signed, thirty-four pages in all;
                dated as follows: "Camp Stoneman M.d April 30th /64"; "Camp Stoneman May 5th /64";
                "Camp Stoneman Oposite Washington City May 10th /64"; "White House Landing V.a June
                8th 1864"; "Plymouth Mich. At Home Oct 2d /64"; "Plymouth Mich. Nov 7th 1864";
                "Plymouth Mich. Nov. 21th /64"; "Washington City D.C Thursday Eve June 16" (Bucke
                has added "1865(?)"); "Feb 11th 1875"; "March 5th .75"; "Aug 16th 1875." With typed
                copies of a letter written by Bucke to Farwell, dated "London, Ont., 14th Oct.,
                1898," and of an unsigned and undated note written by Whitman to Farwell, annotated
                by Bucke. Several of Farwell's letters are endorsed in Whitman's autograph. Bound in
                a small folio volume, cloth, orange morocco back.

